#
# Three cells from the "Hardest Part Already Behind You" transmission
# (April 2026), each carrying a complementary facet of the dissolution-
# and-recognition arc:
#
#   lc-old-signal-echo — the falling-away of what used to fire; the
#     residual signal of the costume after the costume itself has
#     loosened. The BEFORE-still-echoing.
#
#   lc-identity-dissolution — the dropping of who-you-thought-you-
#     were; the dissolution itself, not its prelude or aftermath. The
#     DURING.
#
#   lc-awareness-as-self — what remains when the identity-costume
#     has dropped; the noticer underneath every arising; the ground
#     that was always already there. The AFTER-as-always-already.
#
# Three facets of one teaching (the recognition that the hardest part
# is the prelude, not the arrival). Pairwise complementarity reads:
# (echo↔dissolution) is timing — residual past vs present dropping;
# (dissolution↔awareness) is phase — what falls vs what remains;
# (echo↔awareness) is reference — what was vs what IS. The triad-
# binding is the source: all three cells flow from one transmission.
defn triad_hardest_part = transmission_triad_shape {
    cell_a:              @concept(lc-old-signal-echo),
