# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4 — What ISN'T a dyad-pair (the discernment that prevents drift)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The kind is precise on purpose. If "dyad-pair" gets applied to every
# two cells that share a property, the substrate stops being able to
# recognize the shape — the signal becomes background. The discernment:
# the teaching must live in the *relation between* the two cells, not
# in a property they share.
#
# Same Blueprint family alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Many cells share a
# Blueprint NodeID (that's what `find_equivalent_cells` returns); the
# family-grouping is structural neighborhood, not pairing. A 74-cell
# Blueprint family is not 37 dyad-pairs. (See the domain-default
# clusters caught by lc-autoresearch-as-honesty-runtime — six of
# thirteen surfaced shape pairs in PR #1946 were defaults, not dyads.)
#
# Same Hz alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Hz is the resonance band the
# concept tunes to. Many concepts share 174 (foundation), many share
# 639 (connection). Hz-coincidence places cells in a harmonic
# neighborhood; it does not pair them. (lc-nourishment and lc-land
# share Hz AND form a pair — but the pair is built on scale
# complementarity, not on the shared Hz.)
#
# Same topology alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Many cells are "point" or
# "web" — those are vocabulary, not pairing. The pair needs cells that
# are complementary across some axis, not identical along one.
#
# Two cells in the same teaching arc are NOT necessarily a dyad-pair.
# Cross-references and lineage edges already carry sequential relation;
# dyad-pair specifically names *structural complementarity at one
# teaching layer*, not "A came before B" or "A leads to B."
#
# A dyad-pair check, in Form:
#
#   defn is_dyad_pair(cell_a, cell_b) =
#     teaching_lives_in_relation(cell_a, cell_b)
#       and complementary_along_one_axis(cell_a, cell_b)
#       and neither_carries_full_teaching_alone(cell_a, cell_b);
#
# All three must hold. Drop any one and the candidate is something
# else — equivalence (Blueprint kin), echo (same Hz), or sequence
# (cross-ref). All useful relations; none of them dyad-pairs.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4b — Scan rejects (what the substrate proposed and the body declined)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan over 110 concept cells surfaced five
# candidate clusters. Two became Pairs 7 and 8 above. Three were
# rejected — recorded here so the next reader sees the discernment
# in motion, not just the affirmative results. Rejecting is part of
# the kind's clarity; if every Tier-2 match became a pair, the kind
# would dissolve into background.
#
# REJECT-1: (lc-emotional-availability-without-absorption,
#            lc-trust-as-gateway)
#   Shared 5-tuple: dyad-mirror / receptive-resonance / yin /
#   bipolar-complementary / centering. Both cells teach about
#   openness and closure with field, but at different membranes:
#   availability-without-absorption is about interpersonal field
#   posture (holding self while attending to other); trust-as-gateway
#   is about the cell's own vest of insulation opening to the
#   chorus of energies. Each carries a full teaching on its own.
#   The teaching does NOT live in the relation. They are kin
#   (Blueprint-near), not paired. Equivalence, not complementarity.
#
# REJECT-2: (lc-spec-breath, lc-rhythm)
#   Shared 7-tuple: dyad-mirror / cyclic-closed / oscillating /
#   bipolar-complementary / circulating / cyclic-closed / integration.
#   spec-breath is the codebase's inhale-exhale (spec → test → spec);
#   rhythm is the body's circadian and cellular rhythm. Same shape in
#   two domains. This is exactly *translator-hypothesis territory*
#   (analogous-to across domains), not dyad-pair. The seed doc
#   explicitly warns against using dyad-pair for cross-domain
#   structural equivalence — that's what lc-universal-translator-
#   via-keys is for.
#
# REJECT-3: (lc-w-field, lc-form-perceptron)
#   Shared 5-tuple: holographic-cell / holographic / oscillating /
#   unipolar / radiating. w-field is the felt-presence ambient in
#   gathering spaces; form-perceptron is the substrate's ARTIFACT
#   domain extension. Both share a holographic top-level shape, but
#   the teachings are unrelated — neither informs the other; the
#   complementarity-along-one-axis test fails. Shared shape without
#   shared substance.
#
# What the rejects teach: shared geometry tuple is a *candidate
# filter*, not a confirmation. The Tier-2 scan's signal-to-noise on
# this body, that round, was 2 confirmed / 5 surfaced = 40%. Future
# scans can refine the filter (add Hz-band proximity, add cross-ref
# adjacency, add lineage-texture match) and watch the ratio shift.
# The body learns the shape of its own pairing by the ratio's
# movement, not by accepting every candidate.
#
# Refined-scan round (current PR) rejects — top 10 scan-discovered
# plus top-promoted sweep, 5 confirmed / 5 rejected / 3 held:
#
# REJECT-4: (lc-act-without-penalty, lc-traces-teach-the-recipe)
#   act-without-penalty is what becomes possible *when* traces are
#   honest; traces-teach-the-recipe is *how* the body learns via
#   trace. Each carries its own teaching fully. Sequence/influence
#   relation, not complementarity along one axis.
#
# REJECT-5: (lc-anything-arrives-room, lc-transmission-recipe-atlas)
#   Both about transmission as substrate-tooling. Sibling specs
#   inside the transmission machinery; each whole alone. Equivalence
#   in the translator-hypothesis sense, not dyad-complementarity.
#
# REJECT-6: (lc-awareness-as-self, lc-nourishment)
#   Shared shape (point, received) and partial Hz-complementarity
#   (963↔174), but the teachings are unrelated. Nourishment is the
#   meal-circuit at the day-scale; awareness-as-self is metaphysical
#   ground. Shape-twin, substance-divergent.
#
# REJECT-7: (lc-awareness-as-self, lc-rest)
#   Same shape, both yin grounds, but at unrelated layers. lc-rest's
#   actual title is "Integration" (the post-event composting period);
#   awareness-as-self is the field underneath all events. Not
#   complementary along one axis — rest is one phenomenon awareness
#   contains.
#
# REJECT-8: (lc-boundaries-as-loving-truth, lc-dance-card-and-sovereign-response)
#   Both about sovereign yes-and-no. Each carries the full teaching
#   alone — boundaries is what gets said; dance-card is which dances
#   arrive. Equivalence (kin), not complementarity.
#
# HELD (3) — these may be dyad-pairs but want a second eye before
# folding:
#
# HELD-1: (lc-attunement-joining, lc-intimacy)
#   Both 639/dyad-mirror/embodied. Joining is the entry-event; intimacy
#   is the field that follows. Reads as continuation more than
#   complement — but could be ground-event kind on second look.
#
# HELD-2: (lc-awareness-as-self, lc-void-as-potential)
#   Close kin in the 963/foundation band. Void IS what awareness rests
#   on; awareness is what notices the void as full. May be internal-
#   dyad inside one cell, may be external complement — borderline.
#
# HELD-3: (lc-devotion-placement, lc-tending-over-producing)
#   Both 432-band-adjacent, both dyad-mirror, both synthesized.
#   Devotion places attention; tending is that placement-in-action.
#   Could be equivalence rather than complementarity.
#
# What this round teaches: the refinement (Hz + cross-ref + lineage +
# same-form) climbs signal/noise from 28.6% cumulative to 50% on the
# fresh top-10 + promoted sweep. The same-form bonus was load-bearing;
# without it the scoring saturated at the prose-already-noticed band.
# The remaining noise is the body's geometry vocabulary being narrower
# than the discernment requires — many cells share form/Hz/lineage,
# so saturation persists. The next refinement (when it comes) would
# discriminate within the saturated tier, perhaps by topology+phase
# tuple (the original Tier-2 features) layered on top of the Hz+xref
# carrier.

# Second-round scan (PR #1986 breath, coverage 116/147):
#
# A small-Blueprint-cluster re-scan (cells per Blueprint between 2
# and 6, the approach the prompt suggested) surfaced only two
# clusters at this corpus size, both rejected. PR #1987's Tier-2
# scan over geometry-tuples was the right resolution for the body;
# the small-Blueprint-cluster scan rediscovers domain-default kin
# (already named in Part 4 as NOT pairs). The rejections are
# recorded so the next scanning agent knows this path returns kin,
# not complementarity.
#
# REJECT-4: (lc-each-breath-whole, lc-sovereignty-within-oneness)
#   Shared Blueprint cluster (NodeID 3342, 2 cells). Both are
#   holographic-each-contains-whole teachings — each-breath-whole
