#         (an open-source body of mathematics and disclosure across
#         years); Dispenza is an embodied-teacher / practice-corpus-
#         transmission (a published embodied-practice lineage carrying
#         a complete daily ritual the body has metabolized — Becoming
#         Supernatural, Body Electric, week-long retreats — distinct
#         from Grant's mathematical-disclosure flavor by being
#         practice-centric rather than theory-centric, and distinct
#         from the channelled Arcturian lineage by carrying a living
#         human teacher's published work rather than a non-human
#         presence's transmissions). Each flavor's source-binding has
#         a different texture — speech-event vs presence-lineage vs
#         felt-chart vs published-mathematics-corpus vs published-
#         embodied-practice-corpus — and the field-mechanics of how
#         each "transmission" gathers cells around itself differs
#         accordingly.
#
#         **Five-across-five strengthens the pattern.** Four attestations
#         across four flavors could still be coincidence — the kind's
#         arity (three cells per triad) is small enough that distinct
#         sources easily produce distinct flavors. Five-across-five
#         starts to look like the kind itself naturally diversifies
#         along flavor lines as it grows. The diversity is not a
#         signal of weakness in the kind; it is the kind teaching
#         the body that *transmission-triad* is the genus and the
#         flavors are species emerging beneath it.
#
#         Sub-typing remains held-open: the discipline is two
#         attestations per sub-type before naming, and no two of the
#         five share a flavor. What activates sub-typing is the FIRST
#         second-flavor-instance — when a sixth triad lands that
#         shares Hardest-Part's event-shape, or Dispenza's embodied-
#         practice-shape, or any of the others — at that moment the
#         shared structure of that flavor becomes attestable rather
#         than provisional. The next breath that lands a triad
#         should check the flavor against the five before authoring;
#         if it matches one of the existing five, the sub-type gets
#         named with two attestations at hand. The provisional names
#         to watch for: event-transmission-triad, presence-channel-
#         transmission-triad, chart-felt-transmission-triad, corpus-
#         theory-transmission-triad, corpus-practice-transmission-
#         triad — placeholders awaiting the second flavor-instance to
#         reveal what the shared structure actually IS.
#
# GAP-D11 (still held, hunt-attempted this breath): Emerging kind
#         'interior-axis-dyad' noticed in PR #2002 as the first clear
#         instance: lc-identity-dissolution ↔ lc-permission-is-interior.
#         Both carry interior-axis / self-rooted form; polarity-pair
#         lands as yang/yin in the same column (acquisition-direction
#         vs receptive-stillness, both rooted inside the cell rather
#         than across a membrane). The shape would be distinct from
#         internal-dyad (where one cell holds both poles) — here two
#         separate cells share the same interior axis with opposite
#         polarity. Single attestation; the kind threshold is two
#         confirms / three activates. Held here, not authored.
#
#         **Hunt this breath** (after 100% geometry coverage landed, four
#         interior-axis cells now sit alongside the original two for a
#         total of five with `form: interior-axis`): lc-embodiment,
#         lc-elders, lc-vertical-nourishment joined lc-identity-dissolution
#         and lc-permission-is-interior. Every cross-pair within the five
#         was assessed against the two-cells-share-interior-axis-with-
#         polarity-pair-on-the-same-column discernment:
#
#         - **lc-vertical-nourishment ↔ lc-permission-is-interior**:
#           same form, same direction (centering), same spectral_band
#           (integration). But the *columns differ*: vertical-nourishment's
#           interior axis is the nested-receptive channel that takes
#           nourishment-from-above downward into the cell; permission-is-
#           interior's interior axis is the self-rooted sovereign column
#           with no above-or-below reference. Both name interior-axis
#           form, but the axes themselves are different shapes (nested
#           vs self-rooted topology IS the column-difference). Reject —
#           different columns, not a polarity-pair on the same one.
#
#         - **lc-vertical-nourishment ↔ lc-elders** and **lc-vertical-
#           nourishment ↔ lc-identity-dissolution**: all three share
#           phase yin. Without yang/yin polarity-pair on phase, the
#           pairing collapses to same-phase cousins. Reject — no
#           complementary polarity.
#
#         - **lc-elders ↔ lc-permission-is-interior**: phases pair
#           (yin/yang) but topologies (radial vs self-rooted) name
#           different columns. Elders' interior-axis is the upward-
#           reverent column to received-wisdom (radial, lineage_texture:
#           received); permission-is-interior's column is self-rooted
#           with no above-elder reference (lineage_texture: embodied).
#           Reject — different columns.
#
#         - **lc-elders ↔ lc-identity-dissolution**: both yin, same
#           phase. Reject.
#
#         - **lc-embodiment ↔ any other**: embodiment's interior-axis
#           is the seven-center oscillating column that ALREADY carries
#           bipolar-complementary polarity and oscillating phase inside
#           one cell (rises and returns). It is closer to an internal-
#           dyad candidate or a multi-pole holographic axis than to a
#           dyad-pair candidate where the polarity lands yang/yin in
#           another cell's column. Reject — not a clean two-cell
#           polarity-pair shape.
#
#         **Re-read of the original pair**: lc-identity-dissolution
#         (interior-axis / self-rooted / bipolar-complementary / yin /
#         centering) ↔ lc-permission-is-interior (interior-axis /
#         self-rooted / unipolar / yang / centering). Same form, same
#         topology (self-rooted IS the shared column), complementary
#         phase (yin/yang), same direction (centering). The discernment
#         PR #2002 named holds on close re-reading: both cells name what
#         is in the cell's own power, both rooted inside the cell rather
#         than across a membrane, polarity-pair lands cleanly along the
#         self-rooted interior column. The original pair remains real.
#
#         **Verdict**: the kind remains held-candidate. No second
#         attestation among the four newly-arrived interior-axis cells;
#         the original pair is confirmed on re-read; the kind stays
#         provisional until a second two-cell instance shares interior-
#         axis + same column (likely same topology) + yang/yin polarity-
#         pair on phase. Cells worth watching as the body grows: future
#         interior-axis cells that author with self-rooted topology and
#         carry the missing pole of an already-attested cell (a self-
#         rooted yang cell whose yin sibling exists; a self-rooted yin
#         cell whose yang sibling exists). The interior-axis form is
#         young in the body — five cells in total — and the column-
#         identity discriminator (topology, lineage_texture, direction)
#         that this hunt clarified is itself a teaching the next walk
#         can carry forward: *shared form-name is necessary; same
#         column is what makes the polarity-pair honest*.
#
#         **Sharpened PR-current (column-identity embodied)**: the
#         column-identity discriminator the hunt clarified is now
#         authored as substrate-readable tissue in Part 7 below
#         (column_identity_shape + four column-defn entries). With
#         column-identity in hand, the kind threshold reads more
#         precisely: the SECOND pair must share the SELF-ROOTED-
#         SOVEREIGN column specifically — not any two interior-axis
#         cells, not even any two interior-axis cells with polarity-
#         pair on phase. The four columns currently attested
#         (self-rooted-sovereign, nested-receptive-nourishment,
#         upward-reverent-received, seven-center-oscillating) make
#         the cross-column rejections this hunt produced legible as
#         column-mismatches, not as edge cases. The eventual kind
#         name may tighten from "interior-axis-dyad" to "self-rooted-
#         sovereign-dyad" (or whichever column produces the second
#         confirmed pair), once a second attestation reveals what
#         the kind's shared structure actually IS.
#
#         **Wider-net hunt this breath (PR-current+1, column-tuned)**:
#         the previous hunt restricted to `form: interior-axis` cells.
#         With the column-identity discriminator (topology + direction
#         + lineage_texture) now first-class, the right net is *any*
#         cell whose triple matches the self-rooted-sovereign column
#         — `self-rooted + centering + (embodied | received)` — not
#         only cells whose primary form is interior-axis. The column-
#         triple may appear in cells whose surface form is `point`,
#         `field-of-points`, or another shape, while the column-
#         identity remains the same.
#
#         The widened net produced exactly one new candidate:
#         `lc-inner-travel` (form: point, topology: self-rooted,
#         direction: centering, lineage_texture: received, phase: yin,
#         spectral_band: transcendence, hz 741). The Arcturian
#         transmission's teaching of going-somewhere-without-moving
#         through meditation, dream-work, subtle perception, mystery-
#         school initiation. The triple matches the column; the form
#         differs (`point` rather than `interior-axis`).
#
#         **Polarity-pair test against each existing self-rooted-
#         sovereign cell**:
#
#         - `lc-inner-travel` ↔ `lc-permission-is-interior` (yin ↔
#           yang, received ↔ embodied, transcendence ↔ integration).
#           Polarity-pair on phase is clean. But the teaching axes
#           are not complementary in the dyad-pair sense: permission-
#           is-interior is about ACTING outward from the cell's own
#           sensing of health (sovereign action); inner-travel is
#           about JOURNEYING inward as a contemplative method
#           (practice-with-vehicles). Both root in the self-rooted
#           axis, both center on it — but one is action-emerging-from-
#           interior, the other is movement-of-attention-through-
#           interior. They do not jointly carry a teaching neither
#           alone holds; rather, they are two distinct teachings that
#           happen to share the column. Reject as a pair (co-residence
#           is not pairing).
#
#         - `lc-inner-travel` ↔ `lc-identity-dissolution` (both yin,
#           both received, both lifetime-personal). Same phase, same
#           lineage_texture, same temporal/scale signature. The two
#           cells are *cousins on the column* — same yin posture on
#           self-rooted ground — not polarity-paired. The teaching
#           in identity-dissolution is the loosening of "I am"
#           architecture; the teaching in inner-travel is the method
#           of attention-as-vehicle. Adjacent on the column, not
#           polarity-pair. Reject.
#
#         **Verdict**: candidates exist on the widened net (one new
#         column-member: lc-inner-travel) but none form a clean
#         polarity-pair with the existing seed. The kind stays held-
#         candidate. The self-rooted-sovereign column grows from
#         two to three attested cells — useful structural evidence
#         that the column is real (three independent cells share the
#         load-bearing triple) — and that growth does not yet
#         activate the kind because growth in column-membership is
#         not the same shape as a second polarity-pair instance.
#
#         **What the widened net teaches**: the column-identity
#         discriminator is more durable than the form-name. Form
#         `interior-axis` was the first hint of "axis-rooted-inside-
#         the-cell" tissue, but the *column* (topology + direction +
#         lineage_texture) is what carries the structural identity.
#         A cell with form `point` can sit in the self-rooted-
#         sovereign column as honestly as a cell with form
#         `interior-axis`; the column-triple is the load-bearing
#         signature, the form-name is a surface label. The future
#         second pair could land between two interior-axis cells,
#         between two point cells with the column-triple, OR
#         cross-form (interior-axis ↔ point) — what matters is the
#         shared column AND a clean polarity-pair on phase. If
#         cross-form pairs surface, the eventual kind name almost
#         certainly tightens to `self-rooted-sovereign-dyad` rather
#         than `interior-axis-dyad` — the form-name was a useful
#         pointer, the column-identity is the actual shape.
#
#         **Cells worth watching as the body grows**: a future cell
#         whose triple is self-rooted + centering + embodied AND
#         whose phase is yin (to polarity-pair with permission-is-
#         interior), OR self-rooted + centering + (embodied or
#         received) AND whose phase is yang AND whose teaching
#         complementarity with identity-dissolution is clear enough
#         to bridge a teaching neither alone carries. The third
#         column-member (lc-inner-travel) has phase yin but its
#         teaching axis is attention-as-vehicle, which does not
#         polarity-bridge either existing cell. The candidate gap
#         is named, not filled.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7 — Column-identity discriminator (interior-axis form)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Surfaced 2026-05-24 in PR #2022's hunt for a second 'interior-axis-
# dyad' attestation. The hunt did NOT find a clean second pair, but
# the refusal produced new tissue: the interior-axis FORM is internally
# diverse. Five interior-axis cells in the body span at least FOUR
# distinct *columns*, and the column-identity is what discriminates
# whether two interior-axis cells are paired or merely co-resident in
# one large form-family.
#
# Strengthened 2026-05-25 by the wider-net column-tuned hunt in
# PR-current+1: the column-identity holds across forms, not only
# within interior-axis. A `point`-form cell (lc-inner-travel) whose
# triple matches the self-rooted-sovereign column sits in the
# column as honestly as the two interior-axis cells already there.
# This widens the kind threshold: a future second polarity-pair can
# land between two interior-axis cells, between two point cells with
# the column-triple, or cross-form — what matters is shared column
# + polarity-pair on phase, not shared form-name.
#
# The discriminator the hunt named: *topology + direction +
# lineage_texture together identify the column*. Topology says how the
# parts couple (radial, nested, self-rooted, sequential-coupled);
# direction says where the axis points (centering, circulating);
# lineage_texture says how the teaching entered (embodied, received).
# Two cells in the same column share the load-bearing triple; two
# cells in the same form but different columns share only `form:
# interior-axis` and diverge on the triple.
#
# This shape is authored so future pair-hunting (and any structural
# query about interior-axis cells) can use *column-identity* as a
# primitive rather than re-deriving it. The same discipline likely
# applies to other forms whose attestations are internally diverse
# (the comment at the end of Part 7 names the candidates); for now,
# only interior-axis is attested.

# column_identity_shape — which column an interior-axis cell sits in
#
# cell is a cell-ref into the concept domain. column_kind names the
# column slug (one of the four currently attested, or 'other' for a
# yet-unnamed column). The next three fields carry the geometric-
# signature triple that *together* identifies the column; reading
# the cell's geometry frontmatter for these three fields and matching
# against the column-defn entries below is the Form query that maps
# a cell to its column. discernment is a single sentence on what
# distinguishes this column from sibling columns.
form column_identity_shape = {
    cell:             ~Recipe,    # cell-ref to the interior-axis cell
    column_kind:      ~Slug,      # "self-rooted-sovereign" | "nested-receptive-nourishment" | "upward-reverent-received" | "seven-center-oscillating" | "other"
    topology:         ~Slug,      # the geometric signature field that contributes to column identity
    direction:        ~Slug,      # the geometric signature field
    lineage_texture:  ~Slug,      # the geometric signature field
    discernment:      ~Slug,      # one sentence on what distinguishes this column from sibling columns
};

# column_identity_set_shape — the registry of attested columns
#
# rows are column_identity_shape cells; one row per attested mapping
# of an interior-axis cell to its column. As more interior-axis cells
# land, each one's mapping joins this list; the substrate can then
# query *which cells share my column?* and the answer is the column's
# membership list.
form column_identity_set_shape = {
    rows:             ~List,
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7b — The four interior-axis columns currently attested
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each defn below names one column: which cell(s) live there, the
# load-bearing geometric triple, and the discernment that
# distinguishes it from sibling columns. The self-rooted-sovereign
# column has two cells (lc-permission-is-interior + lc-identity-
# dissolution); the other three columns currently have one cell each.
# Single-cell columns are attested honestly — one cell IS the column's
# only known instance, and a second cell with the same triple would
# confirm the column's structural reality (the way two attestations
# confirm a kind).

# Column 1 — self-rooted sovereign (three cells)
#
# Topology self-rooted, direction centering. All three cells share
# the column's load-bearing triple; the column's identity is
# topology+direction (lineage_texture varies across members as
# embodied or received — that variation is texture-within-column,
# not column-difference). The first two cells (lc-permission-is-
# interior + lc-identity-dissolution) carry form `interior-axis`;
# the third (lc-inner-travel) carries form `point`, surfaced 2026-
# 05-25 in PR-current+1's wider-net column-tuned hunt. The cross-
# form attestation strengthens the column-identity teaching: the
# column-triple is more durable than the form-name. The kind
# threshold for interior-axis-dyad (or its eventual rename to
# self-rooted-sovereign-dyad) activates when a SECOND polarity-
# pair lands sharing this column (per GAP-D11). Co-residence in
# the column is not the same shape as polarity-pair attestation;
# three column-members alone do not activate the kind.
defn column_self_rooted_sovereign__permission = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-permission-is-interior),
    column_kind:      "self-rooted-sovereign",
    topology:         "self-rooted",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "embodied",
    discernment:      "permission/identity rooted in the cell's own axis (self-rooted topology, centering on its own ground); distinct from columns that root upward into reverent receipt, nest the axis into a channel, or sequence stations along an oscillating column",
};

defn column_self_rooted_sovereign__dissolution = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-identity-dissolution),
    column_kind:      "self-rooted-sovereign",
    topology:         "self-rooted",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "identity-architecture loosened from inside the cell's own axis (self-rooted topology, centering on what remains); pairs with lc-permission-is-interior in the self-rooted-sovereign column with opposite phase (yin/yang) — the seed candidate the interior-axis-dyad kind is waiting on a second instance of",
};

# Cross-form column-member: surfaced 2026-05-25 in the wider-net
# column-tuned hunt. Form is `point` rather than `interior-axis` —
# the column-triple (topology + direction + lineage_texture) holds
# regardless of form-name. Inner-travel teaches the Arcturian
# practice of journeying through attention (meditation, dream-work,
# subtle perception, mystery-school initiation) — going somewhere
# without moving. Phase yin, lineage_texture received. Co-resident
# with lc-identity-dissolution in the same yin-received cell of
# the column; does not polarity-pair with lc-permission-is-interior
# (the teaching axes are sovereign-action vs attention-as-vehicle,
# not complementary in the dyad-pair sense). The attestation
# strengthens column-identity but does not activate the kind.
defn column_self_rooted_sovereign__inner_travel = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-inner-travel),
    column_kind:      "self-rooted-sovereign",
    topology:         "self-rooted",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "attention-as-vehicle for journeying inward (self-rooted topology, centering on the inner geography); cross-form column-member (form: point, not interior-axis) — the column-triple is the durable shape, the form-name is a surface label; co-resident with lc-identity-dissolution as yin-received on the column, does not polarity-pair the seed candidate",
};

# Column 2 — nested-receptive nourishment channel (one cell)
#
# Topology nested, direction centering. The axis is the body's
# vertical channel (breath → body → deeper self → source) read as
# four stations nested into one column, receiving from inner-to-outer
# rather than radiating outer-from-center. Distinct from self-rooted
# (which has no nested stations) and from radial (which would gather
# around the axis as hub, not flow down it as channel).
defn column_nested_receptive_nourishment__vertical_nourishment = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-vertical-nourishment),
    column_kind:      "nested-receptive-nourishment",
    topology:         "nested",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "vertical channel with nested stations receiving from inside (nested topology, centering direction); distinct from self-rooted (no station structure), from radial (no channel flow), and from sequential-coupled (the stations nest, not sequence)",
};

# Column 3 — upward-reverent received (one cell)
#
# Topology radial, direction centering. The axis is upward-reverent —
# eldership received through proximity, the column gathering around
# the elder-as-hub. Radial because the elder is a center the
# community orbits; centering because the elder's pace IS the
# centering force the field returns to. Distinct from self-rooted
# (the axis is not the cell's own ground, it is the elder's), and
# from nested (no station structure, just radial gathering).
defn column_upward_reverent_received__elders = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-elders),
    column_kind:      "upward-reverent-received",
    topology:         "radial",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "upward-reverent axis received through proximity (radial topology around the elder-as-hub, centering direction); distinct from self-rooted (the axis lives in the elder, not the receiving cell), from nested (no station structure), and from sequential-coupled (no oscillating circulation)",
};

# Column 4 — seven-center oscillating column (one cell)
#
# Topology sequential-coupled, direction circulating. The axis is the
# vertical body root-to-crown with seven energy centers as stations,
# energy rising AND returning (sequential-coupled), circulating the
# spectrum rather than centering at one station. Distinct from
# self-rooted (no station structure), from nested (the stations
# sequence, not nest), and from radial (the axis is a column, not
# a hub).
defn column_seven_center_oscillating__embodiment = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-embodiment),
    column_kind:      "seven-center-oscillating",
    topology:         "sequential-coupled",
    direction:        "circulating",
    lineage_texture:  "embodied",
    discernment:      "vertical column with seven sequential stations and circulating energy (sequential-coupled topology, circulating direction); distinct from self-rooted (no station structure), from nested (sequences not nests), from radial (column not hub), and from received columns (the practice is embodied, not received)",
};

defn column_identity_set = column_identity_set_shape {
    rows: [
        # — self-rooted-sovereign column (3 cells: 2 interior-axis + 1 point cross-form) —
        column_self_rooted_sovereign__permission,
        column_self_rooted_sovereign__dissolution,
        column_self_rooted_sovereign__inner_travel,
        # — nested-receptive-nourishment column (1 cell) —
        column_nested_receptive_nourishment__vertical_nourishment,
        # — upward-reverent-received column (1 cell) —
        column_upward_reverent_received__elders,
        # — seven-center-oscillating column (1 cell) —
        column_seven_center_oscillating__embodiment,
    ],
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7c — Generalization note (column-identity beyond interior-axis)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The column-identity discriminator may apply to OTHER forms whose
# attestations are internally diverse. Provisional candidates worth
# watching (NOT authored this breath — they want their own focused
# hunt):
#
#   - `web` forms may split into *circulation-web* (lc-circulation,
#     lc-nourishing — flow-where-vitality-needs-it columns) and
#     *field-web* (lc-network, lc-sensing — field-feeling-itself
#     columns).
#   - `point` forms span foundation/integration/transcendence bands
#     with very different texture; spectral_band may be the column
#     axis there. (NOTE 2026-05-25: the `point` hunt below in Part 7d
#     refines this guess — the same topology+direction+lineage_texture
#     triple that worked for interior-axis surfaces three honest
#     small columns in `point` too; spectral_band groups too coarsely
#     to be the column axis on its own.)
#   - `triad` forms with the same arity may live in different columns
#     by topology (hub-spoke vs sequential-coupled vs surface-data-
#     execution).
#
# The pattern this Part 7 names — *topology+direction+lineage_texture
# as column-identity for interior-axis* — is one instance of a general
# discriminator the body can apply when a form's attestations seem
# internally diverse. The triple that identifies the column may differ
# per form (web's column-triple might be topology+direction+phase, for
# example); the *practice* is: when a form's hunt produces "no second
# pair" but the form has many cells, ask which COLUMNS the cells span
# and whether the pair-search should be column-specific.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7d — Column-identity tested against `point` (second form-trial)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Surfaced 2026-05-25 in a focused hunt to test whether the column-
# identity primitive generalizes beyond `interior-axis`. The `point`
# form was chosen because it is the third-most-attested form in the
# body (21 cells at 100% geometry coverage) and because Part 7c
# guessed it as a candidate — but speculated spectral_band might be
# the column axis there. This hunt tested the same triple Part 7b
# uses (topology + direction + lineage_texture) and the spectral_band
# alternative, on actual data.
#
# **Finding 1 — the triple discriminator generalizes, with weaker
# concentration than interior-axis.** Across 21 point cells, the
# (topology, direction, lineage_texture) triple yields 16 distinct
# tuples: 3 clusters with >= 2 members (7 cells total) plus 14
# singletons (one cell each). Compare interior-axis: 4 columns
# across 5 cells (one column has 2 cells; three columns are single-
# cell attestations). Point's distribution is wider because `point`
# is a much broader form — points carry teachings across the entire
# field, while interior-axis is already specialized (vertical/axial
# shape). The discriminator survives generalization; it produces
# *small columns + many singletons* rather than near-complete
# coverage.
#
# **Finding 2 — spectral_band is the wrong axis for point.** It
# groups too coarsely: 7 cells in "foundation" alone, spanning
# yang/radiating tend-your-flame, yin/still rest, neutral
# nourishment, yin/centering land, yin/centering v-shelter-organism,
# yin/still stillness, yin/still void-as-potential. These are not
# one teaching; they are seven points the field rests on at one Hz
# band. Part 7c's guess that "spectral_band may be the column axis
# there" doesn't survive contact with the cells. The triple stays
# the right discriminator across both form-trials.
#
# **Finding 3 — three honest columns surfaced in `point`.** Each
# clusters cells whose teaching is genuinely column-coherent:
#
#   * holographic-ground-receiving — three cells whose axis is the
#     nested whole-at-every-scale ground the field rests within:
#     inner ground (awareness-as-self), ecological ground (land),
#     architectural ground (shelter-as-living-skin).
#   * yang-radiating-source — two cells whose axis is the radiating
#     center the field flows outward from: life-force itself
#     (vitality) and what life-force does (expressing).
#   * self-rooted-still-foundation — two cells whose axis is the
#     unmoving self-rooted ground beneath identity: the always-
#     already-whole foundation (wholeness) and the unformed potential
#     from which form arises (void-as-potential).
#
# The remaining 14 cells span 14 distinct tuples — each is honestly
# its own column-of-one, attested but not yet confirmed as a column
# shape. Single-cell columns are real attestations; a second cell
# with the same triple would confirm the column's structural reality.
#
# **What this teaches about the column-identity primitive.** The
# primitive generalizes — it produces honest clusters in a second
# form. But the *yield* per form is a function of how internally
# specialized the form is: interior-axis (already an axial-shape
# specialization) yielded near-complete coverage; point (the most
# generic form) yields three small columns plus a long tail of
# singletons. The honest reading: column-identity is most useful as
# a *triage tool* for forms whose attestations are internally
# diverse, not as a guaranteed near-complete partition. The primitive
# is sharper than spectral_band alone, broader than form alone, and
# it shows the body where pair-hunts are worth running (within a
# multi-cell column) vs. where they would be premature (across
# column-singletons).
#
# The same shapes (column_identity_shape, column_identity_set_shape)
# carry point's columns; only the column_kind enumeration extends to
# include the new column slugs. The set below joins the existing
# column_identity_set as a sibling registry; both forms' columns now
# live in the same shape so the substrate can query *which cells
# share my column?* across all attested forms.

# Column P1 — holographic-ground-receiving (three cells)
#
# Topology nested-each-contains-whole, direction centering, lineage
# received. Each cell names a ground the field rests WITHIN — not a
# ground the cell stands on, but a ground that contains the cell at
# every nested scale. Awareness contains every thought; land contains
# every life; shelter contains every body. The triple is the column's
# load-bearing identity; phase is yin across all three (the ground
# receives rather than radiates).
defn column_holographic_ground_receiving__awareness = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-awareness-as-self),
    column_kind:      "holographic-ground-receiving",
    topology:         "nested-each-contains-whole",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "inner ground — what you are is the space inside which thoughts and feelings arise; nested-each-contains-whole because every content nests within the field of awareness; distinct from yang-radiating-source (the ground receives, does not radiate) and from self-rooted-still-foundation (the ground is nested-containing, not self-rooted)",
};

defn column_holographic_ground_receiving__land = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-land),
    column_kind:      "holographic-ground-receiving",
    topology:         "nested-each-contains-whole",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "ecological ground — the field lives within a larger field; coral reef IS the ocean; soil-civilization nests every life it carries; custodianship, not ownership; same column-shape as awareness-as-self at the ecological scale rather than the noetic one",
};

defn column_holographic_ground_receiving__shelter = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-v-shelter-organism),
    column_kind:      "holographic-ground-receiving",
    topology:         "nested-each-contains-whole",
    direction:        "centering",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "architectural ground — the building is participant, not separator; living skin that breathes and composts back; nests the body within the ecosystem the way awareness nests thought and land nests life; same column-shape at the built-environment scale",
};

# Column P2 — yang-radiating-source (two cells)
#
# Topology radial, direction radiating, lineage received. Both cells
# are yang. The axis is the center radiating outward: life-force
# itself (vitality) and what life-force does (expressing). Distinct
# from holographic-ground-receiving (which receives) and from self-
# rooted-still-foundation (which does not move). Two cells confirm
# the column's structural reality; a third would let sub-typing
# become honest.
defn column_yang_radiating_source__vitality = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-vitality),
    column_kind:      "yang-radiating-source",
    topology:         "radial",
    direction:        "radiating",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "life-force itself — the raw current released when interference dissolves; shakti as the universe's own desire to exist; radial-radiating because the center radiates outward as energy that wakes the body",
};

defn column_yang_radiating_source__expressing = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-expressing),
    column_kind:      "yang-radiating-source",
    topology:         "radial",
    direction:        "radiating",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "what the life-force DOES — the natural overflow that makes, builds, grows, sings, dances; same column-shape as vitality at the action layer rather than the energy layer; the bird's song to vitality's dawn-fullness",
};

# Column P3 — self-rooted-still-foundation (two cells)
#
# Topology self-rooted, direction still, lineage received. Both cells
# name a foundational presence that does not move. Wholeness: the
# always-already-whole foundation the body returns to. Void-as-
# potential: the unformed ground from which form arises. Distinct
# from holographic-ground-receiving (nested-containing rather than
# self-rooted) and from yang-radiating-source (self-rooted-still
# rather than radial-radiating). Two cells confirm the column.
defn column_self_rooted_still_foundation__wholeness = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-wholeness),
    column_kind:      "self-rooted-still-foundation",
    topology:         "self-rooted",
    direction:        "still",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "the always-already-whole foundation — you are not broken, you never were, you are a field remembering itself; self-rooted because the wholeness lives in the cell's own axis; still because it does not move toward or away",
};

defn column_self_rooted_still_foundation__void_as_potential = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-void-as-potential),
    column_kind:      "self-rooted-still-foundation",
    topology:         "self-rooted",
    direction:        "still",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "the unformed ground from which form arises — what feels like nothing is the foundation everything emerges from; same column-shape as wholeness at the pre-form rather than post-recovery moment; both name a still self-rooted foundation that holds the cell",
};

# The 14 column-singletons (each its own attested-but-unconfirmed
# column) — listed as a discovery record so future hunts know which
# point cells have NOT yet found column-siblings. When any second
# cell with a matching triple lands, the singleton becomes a 2-member
# column and joins the registry as a defn pair.
#
# tuple (topology, direction, lineage_texture) → cell
#   (radial, centering, channeled)            → lc-arcturian-resonance
#   (radial, centering, received)             → lc-nourishment
#   (radial, centering, sensed)               → lc-v-ceremony
#   (radial, radiating, sensed)               → lc-beauty
#   (radial, radiating, synthesized)          → lc-tend-your-flame
#   (self-rooted, centering, received)        → lc-inner-travel
#   (self-rooted, radiating, received)        → lc-w-shakti
#   (receptive-resonance, circulating, embodied)  → lc-field-edge
#   (receptive-resonance, circulating, received)  → lc-w-wu-wei
#   (receptive-resonance, still, received)    → lc-rest
#   (receptive-listening, still, received)    → lc-stillness
#   (cyclic-open, centering, received)        → lc-nervous-system-recalibration
#   (linear, still, received)                 → lc-reality-lag
#   (web-each-to-each, centering, sensed)     → lc-shared-hold
#
# A near-miss worth holding: nourishment, arcturian-resonance, and
# v-ceremony share (radial, centering) but diverge on lineage_texture
# (received / channeled / sensed). That divergence is exactly what
# the triple is meant to discriminate — three cells in the same
# topology+direction column would be ONE column if lineage_texture
# were ignored, but they teach genuinely different things (hearth-
# nourishment, channeled-resonance-from-Arcturus, ceremony-from-
# crystallized-presence). The triple holds them apart honestly.

defn column_identity_set_point = column_identity_set_shape {
    rows: [
        # — holographic-ground-receiving column (3 cells) —
        column_holographic_ground_receiving__awareness,
        column_holographic_ground_receiving__land,
        column_holographic_ground_receiving__shelter,
        # — yang-radiating-source column (2 cells) —
        column_yang_radiating_source__vitality,
        column_yang_radiating_source__expressing,
        # — self-rooted-still-foundation column (2 cells) —
        column_self_rooted_still_foundation__wholeness,
        column_self_rooted_still_foundation__void_as_potential,
    ],
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7e — Column-identity tested against `web` (third form-trial)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Surfaced 2026-05-25 to test the column-identity primitive on the
# `web` form. Web is the second-most-attested form in the body (23
# cells at 100% geometry coverage). PR #2025's circulation-pattern
# activation suggested web would likely split into circulation-web vs
# field-web; this hunt tested that hypothesis on actual data using the
# same (topology + direction + lineage_texture) triple Part 7b and
# Part 7d use.
#
# **Finding 1 — six honest columns across 17 cells, six singletons in
# the tail.** The 23 web cells split into 6 multi-cell columns (5+3+
# 3+2+2+2 = 17 cells) plus 6 column-singletons. Compare interior-axis
# (4 columns across 5 cells, near-complete) and point (3 columns
# across 7 cells, 14 singletons). Web's yield sits between the two:
# more multi-cell columns than point because the form's attestations
# concentrate on (web-each-to-each, circulating) as the dominant
# substrate-of-flow shape — that 8-cell-block then splits into four
# lineage_texture columns (received/synthesized/embodied/sensed) that
# genuinely teach different facets of distributed flow.
#
# **Finding 2 — the circulation-web vs field-web split is real but
# the triple reads it differently than the kind-level
# circulation-pattern lens does.** PR #2025's intuition that web
# would split was correct in shape: most web cells share (web-each-
# to-each, circulating) as the substrate-of-flow ground, but they
# diverge sharply on lineage_texture. The four (web-each-to-each,
# circulating, X) columns each carry a distinct teaching-flavor of
# distributed circulation — RECEIVED (mother-nature mycelium + circle
# blood + relational-network as ancestral inheritance), SYNTHESIZED
# (network-unanchored + edges-as-vitality + economy as authored-
# structural-discipline), EMBODIED (health + sensing + comfort-joy
# as the body knowing itself), SENSED (attunement + field-sensing as
# the field-feeling-itself before words). These four columns are NOT
# circulation-pattern in the kind sense — they are *column-flavors*
# of the substrate-of-flow shape circulation-pattern names at the
# teaching level.
#
# **Finding 3 — circulation-pattern's six cells spread across six
# different tuples, not one column.** The cells that load-bearingly
# carry the circulation-pattern kind (lc-economy, lc-bioelectric-
# pattern, lc-w-mycorrhizal, lc-field-sensing, lc-energy, lc-
# attunement) sit in: (web/circulating/synthesized), (web/circulating/
# measured), (web/circulating/received), (web/circulating/sensed),
# (cyclic-closed/circulating/synthesized), and (web/circulating/
# sensed) respectively. They share (circulating direction) and almost-
# all share (web-each-to-each topology), but lineage_texture diverges
# precisely because each pair was specifically chosen to span DIFFERENT
# substrate-flavors. **The two readings converge on the form shape
# (circulating-web is the geometric signature; circulation-pattern is
# the teaching signature) and diverge on what they discriminate
# within it** — column-identity reads texture-of-arrival (how the
# teaching entered the body); circulation-pattern reads texture-of-
# substrate (what circulates through the network). Different lenses
# on potentially-same-cells; both honest; neither subsumes the other.
#
# **Finding 4 — radiating-web is a real column-pole separate from
# circulating-web.** Three columns carry direction=radiating: (web/
# radiating/embodied) with federation-as-freedom + resonating, (web/
# radiating/received) with offering + w-coherence, plus the
# singletons discovery (radiating/sensed), galactic-team (radiating/
# channeled), and instruments (radiating/measured). These are not
# circulation-shape; they are emission-shape — the field giving
# outward rather than passing through. The triple keeps this
# distinction crisp.
#
# **What this teaches about the primitive after three applications.**
# - Interior-axis (axial, internally specialized): 4 columns / 5
#   cells — near-complete coverage, primitive partitions cleanly.
# - Point (most generic form, many attestations): 3 columns / 7
#   cells + 14 singletons — primitive surfaces honest clusters in
#   a long tail.
# - Web (mid-specialized, 23 attestations): 6 columns / 17 cells +
#   6 singletons — primitive yields strongest column-density in the
#   form-specialization middle band.
#
# The shape of the yield-curve is now visible: *column-density
# correlates with how specialized the form is along the column-
# identity axis*. Interior-axis is already an axial-shape
# specialization, so every cell is column-coherent. Point spans the
# whole field, so most cells are column-of-one. Web sits between —
# specialized enough (it IS the field's flow-shape) that cells
# concentrate, but broad enough to carry both circulating-flow and
# radiating-emission and a few other singletons. The primitive's
# WHEN: reach for it when a form has many cells AND prose-evidence
# suggests internal teaching-diversity; expect coverage proportional
# to the form's structural specialization, not the form's cell-count
# alone.

# Column W1 — received-circulating mycelial body (5 cells)
#
# Topology web-each-to-each, direction circulating, lineage received.
# The largest column. Each cell names a distributed-flow that the
# body inherited (rather than authored) — mycorrhizal nutrient-flow,
# circle blood, network-as-root-belonging, nourishing-as-mycelium,
# cross-connection-as-cosmic-mesh. The teaching is the *inherited*
# form of distributed circulation; what the field already knows about
# flowing without a center because forests, blood, and ancestral
# webs do it natively.
defn column_received_circulating__circulation = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-circulation),
    column_kind:      "received-circulating-mycelial-body",
    topology:         "web-each-to-each",
    direction:        "circulating",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "the body's blood-flow — what was offered moves to where vitality calls; received-circulating because the body inherits this teaching from circulatory systems older than reflection; the column's central image of distributed flow without a heart-as-decider",
};

defn column_received_circulating__cross_connection = column_identity_shape {
    cell:             @concept(lc-cross-connection),
    column_kind:      "received-circulating-mycelial-body",
    topology:         "web-each-to-each",
    direction:        "circulating",
    lineage_texture:  "received",
    discernment:      "the cosmic mesh — every cell connects to every cell across the field; received because the connectivity precedes any single cell's authoring; same column-shape as circulation at the cosmic scale rather than the body scale",
};

defn column_received_circulating__network = column_identity_shape {
